image.altText: Four people on surf boards bobbing in the ocean, beneath a pale blue sky with clouds

items.synopsis: Four Australians and two Indonesian crew whose boat went missing during a surf trip off the coast of Aceh have been found alive after several days at sea, while one crew member is still missing.

title.children: Australians found 'bobbing around on their surf boards' after going missing in Indonesia

items.synopsis: Canberra man Muhammad Arif is charged with allegedly claiming to have explosives on board a Malaysia Airlines flight from Sydney to Kuala Lumpur yesterday.

title.children: 'Confused': Man accused of making explosives threat on Sydney flight doesn't understand charges, court told

image.altText: police on a plane after an incident

items.synopsis: Aviation and security experts weigh in on how in-flight threats of violence are handled, and whose jurisdiction it is to respond.

title.children: 'Our slightest female crew could take down someone quite large': How threatening behaviour on planes is dealt with

image.altText: Salma Paralluelo screams on her knees as Spain teammates run onto the field after a Women's World Cup win.

items.synopsis: After 80 goalless minutes at Eden Park, the first Women's World Cup semifinal explodes to life, with Spain reaching the final after a 2-1 win over Sweden. Follow live.

title.children: Spain scores last-minute stunner against Sweden to reach first Women's World Cup final

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Spain wins 2-1! Spain are in the Women's World Cup final for the first time in their history! The Spanish players are streaming after each other in delirious scenes of joy! Spain had never even won three games in a row at the Women's World Cup! They have now - they're the first team into the World Cup final.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: FULL TIME! SPAIN ARE IN THE WORLD CUP FINAL!

children.content: Spain are in the Women's World Cup final for the first time in their history!
The Spanish players are streaming after each other in delirious scenes of joy!
Spain had never even won three games in a row at the Women's World Cup!
They have now - they're the first team into the World Cup final.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: EXTRAORDINARY! Teresa Abelleira plays the ball out from a corner to Olga Carmona, who side-footed the ball from 25 yards out off the crossbar and in! Incredible goal! Incredible drama!
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 89' GOAL SPAIN!

children.content: Teresa Abelleira plays the ball out from a corner to Olga Carmona, who side-footed the ball from 25 yards out off the crossbar and in!

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: It's the substitute who makes a telling intervention! Rebecka Blomqvist powers home after Hurtig kept a deep cross alive. It's the fourth goal they've scored in the final 15 minutes of a game at this World Cup! They never give up!
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 88' GOAL SWEDEN!

children.content: It's the substitute who makes a telling intervention!
Rebecka Blomqvist powers home after Hurtig kept a deep cross alive.
It's the fourth goal they've scored in the final 15 minutes of a game at this World Cup!

image.altText: Donald Trump stands at a microphone. He is wearing a blue suit and red tie and pictured against a dark background.

items.synopsis: The former US president is indicted over alleged attempts to meddle with the 2020 election results in Georgia. He and 18 allies face a racketeering charge that carries mandatory prison time.

title.children: Trump faces a charge usually aimed at mobsters, with mandatory jail. Here's what we know

image.altText: A fighter jet screams through the air, leaving contrails streaming in its wake.

title.children: Australia entrusted with secret paint that makes fighter jet 'nearly invisible'

image.altText: Schoolgirl holding a trophy.
